Ramayana Ballet on Java (Indonesia)
<i>Ravana (the demon king of Lanka) keeps Sita (Rama's wife) imprisoned - Javanese Ramayana Ballet</i>

<b>The Ramayana is an ancient Sanskrit epic from India and dates back to approximately the 4th century B.C.</b>

The Ramayana tells the story of Rama (an incarnation of the Hindu preserver-God Vishnu), whose wife Sita is abducted by the demon king of Lanka, Ravana. The Javanese Ramayana version differs markedly from the original Hindu prototype - Source: Wikipedia.

Photo taken during the Ramayana Ballet performance at the Purawisata Art and Cultural Center in Yogyakarta (Java, Indonesia).

